<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3264: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-25T16:00:00-05:00">February 25, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>15. Your 19, February 21, 4 p.m. I think it very advisable for President
                            Leguia to make the proposition set forth in the report outlined in your
                            19, February 21, 4 p.m. If this is done, I shall strongly urge Chile to
                            accept. Can you tell when President Leguia will make his
                            proposition?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>